  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0dad\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 1971 \u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Information about trains from 1971",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Railway General Manager Mr. Dhammika Jayasundara said that a hotline number 1971 will be operational from 7.00 am tomorrow (14th) for inquiries and complaints about trains.",
        "The General Manager of Railways said that this phone can be used in all three languages \u200b\u200bSinhala, Tamil and English and all complaints including train running times, seat reservation, fare information, railway security service and reporting railway crossing problems can be directed to it."
      ],
